      "amount": "1 tsp",
      "notes ": "freshly ground black pepper"
    },
    {
      "name": "potatoes",
      "amount": "2 medium",
      "notes ": "diced"
    },
    {
      "name": "dashi powder",
      "amount": "1 tsp",
      " notes": "see recipe notes for dashi extraction information"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "heat a dash of oil in a large deep pot over medium heat. ",
    "add the sliced onion and cook until translucent, about 10 minutes. ",
    "add the minced garlic and cook for another minute, until fragrant. ",
    "add the smoked bacon and cook until crispy, about 5 minutes. ",
    "add the diced black pudding and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes. ",
    "add the diced potatoes, caraway seeds, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper. ",
    "stir to combine and cook for 2 minutes. ",
    "add 1 cup of water and bring to a boil. ",
    "reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. ",
    "season with dashi powder and serve hot."
  ],
